<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 16 at 7:01PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Morgan,
northeastern Jasper and east central Newton Counties through 745 PM
EDT...
At 701 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Mansfield, or 10 miles
southeast of Covington, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Madison, Rutledge, Newborn, Mansfield, Hard Labor Creek State Park
and Farrar.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
